  "text": "The localization of AHA1 and AHA2 proteins at the cellular or tissue level is also likely to elucidate the isoform-specific function of these enzymes during seedling growth. A study of the cell type-specific transcriptome of Arabidopsis roots indicates that AHA1 and AHA2 are highly expressed in the entire root, with some isoform-specific expression. While root hair and epidermal cells express AHA2 more than AHA1, the conducting cells, such as phloem companion and xylem cells, express AHA1 more highly than AHA2 [CITATION_1] . The impaired growth of aha2 mutants on conditions that are likely to stress the PMF seen in this study thus correlates with AHA2 function in solute uptake in root epidermal cells.",
